The paper discusses a method for latent topic analysis, which is a common problem in machine learning and natural language processing. The paper also mentions the use of spectral inference and Joint Stochastic Matrix Factorization (JSMF), which are techniques commonly used in the fields of machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
